HEALTH Minister DR Zweli Mkhize's latest update is that 48 people have now died of the Covid-19 virus in South Africa. The number has jumped by 21 since the last update. The Eastern Cape has registered its first deaths with four and Limpopo with 1. A total of 2605 confirmed cases are in Mzansi. The number of recoveries is increasing,currently sitting at 903. As at today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 2605. pic.twitter.com/eQyQmMRfcp South Africa is still under a lockdown which has been extended by two weeks and could end on April 30.